Author-Name: Brendan K. Beare 
Title: Copulas and Temporal Dependence 
Abstract:
				 An emerging literature in time series
 econometrics concerns the modeling of potentially nonlinear temporal
 dependence in stationary Markov chains using copula functions. We obtain
 sufficient conditions for a geometric rate of mixing in models of this
 kind. Geometric &beta;-mixing is established under a rather strong
 sufficient condition that rules out asymmetry and tail dependence in the
 copula function. Geometric &rho;-mixing is obtained under a weaker
 condition that permits both asymmetry and tail dependence. We verify one
 or both of these conditions for a range of parametric copula functions
 that are popular in applied work.			        Copyright  2010 The Econometric Society. 
