Author-Name: Timothy Besley 
Author-Name: Torsten Persson 
Title: State Capacity, Conflict, and Development 
Abstract:
				 The absence of state capacities to raise
 revenue and to support markets is a key factor in explaining the
 persistence of weak states. This paper reports on an ongoing project to
 investigate the incentive to invest in such capacities. The paper sets out
 a simple analytical structure in which state capacities are modeled as
 forward looking investments by government. The approach highlights some
 determinants of state building including the risk of external or internal
 conflict, the degree of political instability, and dependence on natural
 resources. Throughout, we link these state capacity investments to
 patterns of development and growth. Copyright  2010 The Econometric Society. 
