Author-Name: Donald W. K. Andrews 
Author-Name: Gustavo Soares 
Title: Inference for Parameters Defined by Moment Inequalities Using Generalized Moment Selection 
Abstract:
				 The topic of this paper is inference in
 models in which parameters are defined by moment inequalities and/or
 equalities. The parameters may or may not be identified. This paper
 introduces a new class of confidence sets and tests based on generalized
 moment selection (GMS). GMS procedures are shown to have correct
 asymptotic size in a uniform sense and are shown not to be asymptotically
 conservative. Copyright  2010 The Econometric Society. 
